			<div class="content" id="post-content-4025014">
									

<p>The one thing that dulls this for me is the idea of the DVD format (and drives capable of writing them) persisting for the better part of 100 years&#8230; it's been approximately 20 so far and it's already very much on its way out.</p>
<p>Especially as they apparently outlast both Post-its and permanent markers &#8230; both of which are, for contemporary and often slipcase-stored optical media, rather useful things, never mind their other multifarious uses (and that they have themselves survived 50+ years already).</p>

